08/06/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The defence ministry held a press conference on Wednesday (7 June) to outline plans for assuming some EUFOR responsibilities. These include functions related to the presence of foreign troops and armed civilian groups, and the use of communications and information systems. The ministry and EUFOR will continue to co-ordinate the movement and training of troops and control airspace together. 
In other news, representatives of the OSCE Mission to BiH met with Chief Prosecutor Marinko Jurcevic on Tuesday, to support an initiative for a national strategy on prosecuting war crimes. The document would strictly define the roles of courts and prosecutors' offices, government institutions, NGOs and religious communities in efforts to address the consequences of war crimes. (FENA - 07/06/06)
